This paper is about neural machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The paper proposes a new model for NMT that uses latent variables and deterministic inference, which is a topic that is commonly studied in the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of latent variables and the optimization of the lowerbound is a technique that is also commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of parallelization, which is a topic that is commonly studied in the subfield of neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV).
